  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "MARGARET GORSKY",
    "text": "Exactly. And I think I want to say two other things. One is that I really feel that the children of Holocaust survivors drink those experiences with their mother's milk, and I-- there's really nothing to add to that. I think that, you know, they've imbibed a lot of those experiences through their parents. And also to repeat something that Jana said to me recently. And Jana's now 16 years old. And she said to me that it really scares her that something like that might happen again. And that if she's taken anything from being born into this family, that it's that this should never happen again. That-- And I really feel that, too. That, you know, if there's something-- something good that has arisen out of these terrible ashes, it's that we somehow contribute to make the world a better place.",
